sequenceDiagram
    participant Telegram as Telegram service
    participant Adapter as Telegram adapter
    participant Edge as Gateway edge loop
    participant Queue as Channel queue

    Edge->>Adapter: poll_updates(channel_id, cursor)
    Adapter->>Telegram: getUpdates(bot_token, offset)
    Telegram-->>Adapter: telegram_updates
    Adapter-->>Edge: channel_updates(channel_id, bot_account_id, peer_id, update_id, payload)
    Edge->>Queue: enqueue_inbound(update_id, channel_update)
    Queue-->>Edge: enqueued_or_duplicate
    Edge->>Queue: claim_outbound(gateway_id, lease_ttl)
    alt outbound ready
      Queue-->>Edge: outbound_message(channel_id, peer_id, reply)
      Edge->>Adapter: post_message(channel_id, peer_id, reply)
      Adapter->>Telegram: sendMessage(chat_id, reply)
      Telegram-->>Adapter: send_result(message_id)
      Adapter-->>Edge: delivery_result(message_id)
      Edge->>Queue: mark_outbound_delivered(outbound_id, provider_message_id)
    else no outbound ready
      Queue-->>Edge: none
    end
    Note over Edge,Queue: Edge loop owns external channel IO only and never resolves identity or calls core.
